{"_id":"ANBgWHbSQVgUQecV","name":"Maur","permission":{"default":0},"type":"heritage","data":{"description":"If you want to be from somewhere “foreign” and exotic, choose Maur. Across the ocean to the south, the proud desert kingdoms of Maur are both a military and economic power to be watched with care."},"sort":300000,"flags":{}}
{"_id":"RrvbKXClyyNBYFBB","name":"Altori","permission":{"default":0},"type":"heritage","data":{"description":"If you want to be from somewhere “romantic”, rich in beauty and poetry, choose Altori. Altori are taught from an early age that beauty is the one ideal to be prized above any other. Whether in government, craft, or war, a Altori will execute their duty with precision and poetry. Prone to ritual and careful metaphor, the natives of the distant kingdom are proving exceedingly good at the games of the Ilrienne."},"sort":400000,"flags":{}}
{"_id":"TiL4AssY9Ryty6f9","name":"The Jewel Cities","permission":{"default":0},"type":"heritage","data":{"description":"If you want to be from somewhere “strange”, ancient and arcane, choose to be from The Jewel Cities. Before the three islands, Beryl, Lapis, and Garnet, sunk beneath the waves some years ago, they composed the homes of The Jewel Cities. The culture was rich in advanced technology, and magic was an everyday part of life. Are you Berylyne, Lapyne, or Garnetyne?"},"sort":200000,"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Tk61Y7K84GgQpqPz","name":"Iberican","permission":{"default":0},"type":"heritage","data":{"description":"If you want to be from an unestablished people, choose Iberican. The people of Iberica are often considered nomads. Unsure of you, people in polite society guard their purses a little more closely than usual when you enter the room, even when you’re wearing the trappings of one of the Houses of the Esultare.."},"sort":500000,"flags":{}}
{"_id":"WRzLNozCfzFLg0d6","name":"Calrais","permission":{"default":0},"type":"heritage","data":{"description":"If you want to be from somewhere “wild”, choose Calrais. Calrais is a large country of sprawling grasslands, rugged mountains, and trackless forests. Calrais is too large to be ruled, so government typically extends as far as the edge of a village before dying by inches in the wildlands. Many foreign empires have tried to bring Calrais to heel, but even the Dread Emperor was unable to leash it."},"sort":600000,"flags":{}}
{"_id":"fKEJOkqoAwinyzrm","name":"Ilrienne","permission":{"default":0},"type":"heritage","data":{"description":"If you want to be a native, choose Ilrienne. Ilrien is the greatest city in the world, the very finest of art, culture, and politics blend here. The people are cosmopolitan, vivacious, and quick to trade jokes or draw steel."},"sort":100000,"flags":{}}
